        <!-- 01 Archetype -->
        <div class="bb-section">
          <div class="bb-slabel">01 — Identity & Archetype</div>
          <div class="bb-stitle">WHO IS<br>SGAUGE</div>
          <p style="color:#b8c6d6;font-size:12px;line-height:1.9;max-width:700px;">SGauge is the synthesis of contradictions held without apology. West coast melody filtered through Colorado survival. Engineering precision behind an artist's vulnerability. A father who turned the hardest year of his life into the foundation of everything he's building.</p>
          <div class="bb-archgrid">
            <div class="bb-archcard">
              <div class="bb-archcard-label">Primary Archetype</div>
              <div class="bb-archcard-title">THE SURVIVOR SAGE</div>
              <p>The one who went through it and came back with receipts. Not performing pain — reporting it. The wisdom of a person who had no map and drew their own.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bb-archcard">
              <div class="bb-archcard-label">Secondary Archetype</div>
              <div class="bb-archcard-title">THE BUILDER OUTLAW</div>
              <p>Operates outside the system while building within it. Engineer, developer, A&R, artist — simultaneously. The infrastructure guy who's also the product.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bb-archcard">
              <div class="bb-archcard-label">Sonic Identity</div>
              <div class="bb-archcard-title">UPBEAT PAIN</div>
              <p>West coast melodic influence with a Colorado edge. Vibey enough to sing along to. Heavy enough that you feel the weight underneath. Joy and grief in the same bar.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bb-archcard">
              <div class="bb-archcard-label">Influences</div>
              <div class="bb-archcard-title">THE REFERENCE POINTS</div>
              <p>Mike Posner, Jay Sean, A Boogie wit da Hoodie, Colbie Caillat, Grieves, Slug of Atmosphere. The ones who made something personal feel universal.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Manifesto -->
        <div class="bb-manifesto">
          <div class="bb-slabel" style="margin-bottom:28px;">02 — Artist Manifesto</div>
          <div class="bb-manifesto-text">
            I come from the part of Littleton nobody admits exists. I come from a mother's addiction and a father's prison sentence and a floor that wasn't mine to sleep on. I started rapping because <em>I had something to say and nowhere safe to say it.</em><br><br>
            I became an engineer because I refused to wait for someone else to build my door. I became a developer because I remember what it cost to have no one in my corner. I became RAPDAD because <em>Nelliana deserves a father who turned the worst year of his life into something that outlasts it.</em><br><br>
            I am not performing. I am not a character. I am SGauge — the same person you'll meet in the studio, on the stage, and at the funeral. <em>Maktub. It was written.</em> All of it.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 03 Storyline -->
        <div class="bb-section">
          <div class="bb-slabel">03 — Career Storyline</div>
          <div class="bb-stitle">SAME OL'<br>GAUGE</div>
          <p style="color:#b8c6d6;font-size:12px;line-height:1.9;max-width:700px;margin-bottom:8px;">The arc is a hood story with a survivor's ending. Not glory for glory's sake — redemption as <em style="color:#c8a96e;">stability</em>. The right to stop working regular jobs and finally belong to the industry you've been building from the inside.</p>
          <div class="bb-arctimeline">
            <div class="bb-arcphase">
              <div class="bb-arcnum">I</div>
              <div class="bb-arclabel">Act One</div>
              <div class="bb-arctitle">THE LOST SHEEP</div>
              <p>East Denver born. Littleton raised. Half-homeless at 14, writing on a friend's floor. The music starts as survival — pure need to translate chaos into something that makes sense.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bb-arcphase">
              <div class="bb-arcnum">II</div>
              <div class="bb-arclabel">Act Two</div>
              <div class="bb-arctitle">SCREAMING INTO THE VOID</div>
              <p>The awakening comes. He builds the infrastructure — engineering, production, A&R, media platform, artist development. He feeds everyone. And yet the universe still hasn't fully aligned.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bb-arcphase">
              <div class="bb-arcnum">III</div>
              <div class="bb-arclabel">Act Three</div>
              <div class="bb-arctitle">GLORY RECLAIMED</div>
              <p>Not fame. Not a platinum plaque. <em style="color:#c8a96e;">Belonging.</em> A seat at the table he helped build. The music finally reaches the people it was always meant for.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 04 Alter Egos -->
        <div class="bb-section">
          <div class="bb-slabel">04 — The Characters</div>
          <div class="bb-stitle">THE THREE<br>FACES</div>
          <div class="bb-egogrid">
            <div class="bb-egocard">
              <div class="bb-egoname">SGAUGE</div>
              <div class="bb-egorole">The Core · The Real · The Artist</div>
              <p>Straight Shawn with the filter off. No performance, no persona — just the duality of mixed heritage and lived experience translated into west coast-influenced Colorado sound.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bb-egocard">
              <div class="bb-egoname">SHADY O'RAQ</div>
              <div class="bb-egorole">The Shadow · The Release Valve</div>
              <p>The part that doesn't have to be responsible. Darker, more reckless, less filtered. Not a lie — an extreme. The hood story without the hope at the end.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bb-egocard">
              <div class="bb-egoname">IICYBABII</div>
              <div class="bb-egorole">The Feminine · The Contrast</div>
              <p>The melodic softness fully unleashed. Pure melodic songwriting unconstrained by street credibility. A creative pressure valve.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

