          <div class="bb-stitle">WHY THIS<br>LANDS</div>
          <div class="bb-twocol">
            <ul class="bb-slist">
              <li><strong>Self-sufficient production</strong> — No studio costs. Radio-ready output on demand. Lower barrier, faster output, full creative control.</li>
              <li><strong>Multi-role infrastructure</strong> — SGauge + RAPDAD55 + RapClass creates three entry points into the same ecosystem.</li>
              <li><strong>Built-in credibility gap</strong> — Known as engineer/developer before artist. That tension, when resolved publicly, is a story.</li>
              <li><strong>International traction early</strong> — "A.I." performing overseas. Sync licensing and international markets are natural targets.</li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="bb-slist">
              <li><strong>Differentiated lane</strong> — Documenting survival rather than glorifying the life. A distinction for a generation increasingly tired of the performance.</li>
              <li><strong>Duality as brand pillar</strong> — Mixed race, dual city, upbeat-pain sound, engineer-artist identity. Duality is structural. It's in everything.</li>
              <li><strong>The silence as power</strong> — What SGauge doesn't say about the hardest year is more compelling than what most artists do say.</li>
              <li><strong>RAPDAD as platform multiplier</strong> — Interview access + artist development = relationships + distribution channel.</li>
